name: rxcui
description: RxNorm Unique identifier for concept (concept ID)

name: lui
description: Unique identifier for term (no value provided)

name: sui
description: Unique identifier for string (no value provided)

name: ispref
description: Atom status - preferred (Y) or not (N) for this string within this concept (no value provided)

name: rxaui
description: Unique identifier for atom (RxNorm Atom ID)

name: code
description: 'Most useful' source asserted identifier (if the source vocabulary has more than one identifier), or a RxNorm-generated source entry identifier (if the source vocabulary has none.)

name: suppress
description: Suppressible flag. Values = N, O, Y, or E. N - not suppressible. O - Specific individual names (atoms) set as Obsolete because the name is no longer provided by the original source. Y - Suppressed by RxNorm editor. E - unquantified, non-prescribable drug with related quantified, prescribable drugs. NLM strongly recommends that users not alter editor-assigned suppressibility.

name: cvf
description: Content view flag. RxNorm includes one value, '4096', to denote inclusion in the Current Prescribable Content subset. All rows with CVF='4096' can be found in the subset.
